.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFF9CEF5FFF42FE92FDE4FEF8" blockId="52.[151,1436,258,717]" box="[199,593,294,321]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF9CEF5FFF42FE92FDE4FEF8" bold="true" box="[199,593,294,321]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">
New record for the 
<collectingRegion id="9F00C289FF9CEF5FFE2AFE93FDF9FEF8" box="[431,588,294,321]" country="Brazil" name="Parana" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Paraná State</collectingRegion>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="15DE5FE0FF9CEF5FFF42FEFFFDD6FD75" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFF9CEF5FFF42FEFFFE03FE69" blockId="52.[151,1436,258,717]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF9CEF5FFF42FEFFFEE7FEDC" bold="true" box="[199,338,330,356]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Comments:</emphasis>
<materialsCitation id="EDAC0636FF9CEF5FFEDEFEFEFE07FE69" country="Guyana" location="The" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" specimenCount="1">
The first record of this species after its original description was made by Nasckrecki (2007), in 
<collectingCountry id="25D34CFBFF9CEF5FFF12FEDAFF47FE31" box="[151,242,367,393]" name="Guyana" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Guyana</collectingCountry>
. Here we provide a new record for the species that is not that far from the 
<typeStatus id="827FB2C9FF9CEF5FFBA1FEDAFBE1FE31" box="[1060,1108,367,393]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">type</typeStatus>
locality. 
<location id="581B5AB0FF9CEF5FFB3CFEDAFB50FE31" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:D56DBD7DFF9CEF5FFF12FF23FDD6FD75:581B5AB0FF9CEF5FFB3CFEDAFB50FE31" box="[1209,1253,367,393]" country="Guyana" name="The" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">The</location>
known distribution of 
<taxonomicName id="9AC477E8FF9CEF5FFF6DFE26FE20FE15" authorityName="Emsley" authorityYear="1970" box="[232,405,403,429]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Steirodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dentiferoides">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF9CEF5FFF6DFE26FE20FE15" box="[232,405,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">S. dentiferoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles that of the previous species, as an enormous gap of records 
<locationDeviation id="4CC91549FF9CEF5FFB29FE26FE8BFE69" firstLocation="Amazon" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" secondLocation="Atlantic Forest">between Amazon and Atlantic Forest</locationDeviation>
also exist
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFF9CEF5FFF42FE6FFBCEFD85" blockId="52.[151,1436,258,717]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF9CEF5FFF42FE6FFEE5FE4C" bold="true" box="[199,336,474,500]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Bioacoustic</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="C5FF10EEFF9CEF5FFEE5FE6EFE5DFE4E" box="[352,488,475,502]" captionStart="FIGURE 26" captionStartId="51.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[210,1376,191,1911]" captionTargetId="figure-17@51.[202,1385,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="51" captionText="FIGURE 26. Calling songs of species of Steirodontini and of Enthephippion olivaceum. A–C: Cnemidophyllum citrifolium; D–F: Steirodon dentiferoides; G–I: S. dentiferum. A: sonogram of one echeme; B, E and H: sonogram of one syllable; D and G: sonogram of two isolated syllables; C, F and H: spectrogram of the respective syllable." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550123" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550123/files/figure.png" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Fig. 26D–F</figureCitation>
): Males stridulate only at night, continually emitting syllables that apparently do not form echemes. In the same way as for the anterior species, the syllables are composed by pulses that are sparser in the first half of the syllable then becoming more grouped towards the end of the syllable.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFF9CEF5FFF42FDF2FDE1FDD9" blockId="52.[151,1436,258,717]" box="[199,596,583,609]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF9CEF5FFF42FDF2FE1EFDD9" box="[199,427,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Dominant frequency</emphasis>
: 13 ± 1.9 kHz.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFF9CEF5FFF42FDDEFE5CFD3D" blockId="52.[151,1436,258,717]" box="[199,489,618,645]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF9CEF5FFF42FDDEFEF5FD3D" box="[199,320,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Bandwidth</emphasis>
: 10 ± 0.5 kHz.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFF9CEF5FFF42FD3AFDEAFD11" blockId="52.[151,1436,258,717]" box="[199,607,655,681]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF9CEF5FFF42FD3AFE9BFD10" box="[199,302,655,680]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Duration</emphasis>
: syllable: 0.03 ± 0.002 ms.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFF9CEF5FFF42FD06FDD6FD75" blockId="52.[151,1436,258,717]" box="[199,611,690,717]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF9CEF5FFF42FD06FEEAFD75" box="[199,351,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Mute interval</emphasis>
: Syllable: 16.5 ± 
<geoCoordinate id="38F06AACFF9CEF5FFDA2FD06FDEBFD75" box="[551,606,691,717]" degrees="8.6" direction="south" orientation="latitude" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" precision="5555" value="-8.6">8.6 s</geoCoordinate>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
